Backups that fail to complete within a specified time period (can be decided either programmatically or by the user) should provide some level of warning within the web interface that they have failed.  This is a critical operation, and failure to complete backups is a very high-risk situation.

For information about how backups can potentially fail, see JRA-18018.  In this case, I've been able to cause the backup-process to hang indefinitely through high packet loss between the JIRA instance and the MS SQL server

Currently [this page|http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/v3.13/issue_creation_email.html] states:

{quote}
createusers
    If createusers is set to true, people who don't currently have an account in JIRA will have it created for them. *In JIRA Enterprise, this allows the creator to be notified of subsequent updates to the issue, by configuring the notification scheme to notify the 'Reporter' of updates*.
{quote}

The note about JIRA Enterprise is not correct, you can configure notifications for reporter in professional and standard editions.

